With createElement, you can create an HTML element entirely from scratch using JavaScript and add it to the page’s DOM dynamically. This can be useful when you need to create multiple elements programmatically or when you don’t want to modify existing elements directly.

Here’s an example of how you could create a canvas element and append it to the page’s body using createElement:

// create a canvas element
var canvas = document.createElement(“canvas”);

// set the canvas element’s attributes
canvas.width = 400;
canvas.height = 400;

// add the canvas element to the page’s body
